<promed@promedmail.org>
[The negative results of the current clinically suspected case are preliminary.
Preliminary negative results might be based upon ELISA testing. A positive
ELISA test for FMD virus can be obtained in about 3 hours. To declare a
case finally negative, virus isolation has to be attempted, a procedure
that requires two 48 hours passages in cell culture i.e. 96 hours in total.
- Mod. AS].
